title.rendered: Joburg vs Durban, South African T20 League, 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Team

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Joburg: Reeza Hendricks, Faf du Plessis (c), Neil Brand, Leus du Plooy, Donavon Ferreira (wk), Sibonelo Makhanya, Romario Shepherd, Gerald Coetzee, Alzarri Joseph, Maheesh Theekshana, Aaron Phangiso

Durban: Kyle Mayers, Wiaan Mulder, Quinton de Kock (c & wk), Matthew Breetzke, Heinrich Klaasen, Dwaine Pretorius, Jason Holder, Keemo Paul, Keshav Maharaj, Prenelan Subrayen, Akila Dananjaya

Venue: The Wanderers, Johannesburg

Pitch Report

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 165

2nd innings average score: 184

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Bouncy but a good wicket to bat on

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

When these teams met earlier in the tournament, Donavon Ferreira (82 off 40 and a wicket) and Quinton de Kock (78 off 52) were the captain and vice-captain of the Ultimate Team respectively.

Faf du Plessis enjoys batting at Johannesburg. He has accumulated 555 runs at 40, including the highest score of 119.

Leus du Plooy is Joburg’s second-leading run-scorer (157 at 79). Incidentally, his highest score (75*) of the season came at this very venue.

Heinrich Klaasen has been a part of the Ultimate Team for the last 3 of 4 games. At The Wanderers, he averages an impressive 48 including the highest score of 73*.

It has been a horrendous tournament for Reeza Hendricks till now. He has managed only 58 runs in 6 innings.

Given the shorter square boundary and the evenness of the wicket, 6 half-centuries have been registered at The Wanderers in the last 3 games.

An average of 6 sixes per innings has been launched at the venue in the last 3 games.

1 / 5 ( 3 votes )
